  "title": "Stopping at Plausible",
  "concept": "When the first explanation tested meets a plausibility threshold, search stops there—rarer alternatives remain untested because the initial answer was good enough.",
  "interactiveId": "b95c0030-da5f-4bfa-8273-11006be56723",
  "sourcePieceId": "b77e8406-a000-46ef-8989-dde9bb48a8b4",
  "publishedAt": 1777733739286,
  "voiceScore": 88,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Stopping at Plausible</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --gold: #c9a227;\n    --teal: #1a6b62;\n    --red: #c92727;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 20px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    min-width: 130px;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--teal);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 3ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .hypotheses {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 10px;\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    flex-wrap: wrap;\n  }\n  .hypothesis {\n    flex: 1;\n    min-width: 70px;\n    padding: 12px 8px;\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    text-align: center;\n    background: #fff;\n    transition: all 220ms ease-out;\n    position: relative;\n  }\n  .hypothesis.tested {\n    border-color: var(--teal);\n    background: #e8f4f2;\n  }\n  .hypothesis.stopped-here {\n    border-color: var(--gold);\n    background: #fef9e7;\n    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(201, 162, 39, 0.2);\n  }\n  .hypothesis.untested {\n    opacity: 0.3;\n    background: #f5f5f5;\n  }\n  .hyp-label {\n    font-size: 0.7rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.05em;\n    margin-bottom: 4px;\n  }\n  .hyp-prob {\n    font-size: 1rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: var(--fg);\n  }\n  .status {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 12px 14px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .status strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .hypotheses {\n      flex-direction: column;\n    }\n    .hypothesis {\n      min-width: 100%;\n    }\n    .control label {\n      min-width: 110px;\n      font-size: 0.9rem;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to set the plausibility bar</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Five explanations exist in order of likelihood. Testing stops when one crosses the bar.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"threshold\">Plausibility bar:</label>\n  <input id=\"threshold\" type=\"range\" min=\"25\" max=\"75\" value=\"50\" step=\"5\" aria-describedby=\"threshold-out\">\n  <output id=\"threshold-out\" for=\"threshold\">50%</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"hypotheses\" id=\"hypotheses\">\n  <div class=\"hypothesis\" data-prob=\"65\" data-label=\"A\">\n    <div class=\"hyp-label\">Explanation A</div>\n    <div class=\"hyp-prob\">65%</div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"hypothesis\" data-prob=\"18\" data-label=\"B\">\n    <div class=\"hyp-label\">Explanation B</div>\n    <div class=\"hyp-prob\">18%</div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"hypothesis\" data-prob=\"9\" data-label=\"C\">\n    <div class=\"hyp-label\">Explanation C</div>\n    <div class=\"hyp-prob\">9%</div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"hypothesis\" data-prob=\"5\" data-label=\"D\">\n    <div class=\"hyp-label\">Explanation D</div>\n    <div class=\"hyp-prob\">5%</div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"hypothesis\" data-prob=\"3\" data-label=\"E\">\n    <div class=\"hyp-label\">Explanation E</div>\n    <div class=\"hyp-prob\">3%</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"status\" id=\"status\">\n  Tested: <strong id=\"tested-count\">0</strong> of 5. \n  Stopped at: <strong id=\"stopped\">—</strong>.\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">Testing proceeds in order of likelihood until one explanation crosses the plausibility bar.</p>\n\n<script>\n(function () {\n  var thresholdSlider = document.getElementById('threshold');\n  var thresholdOut = document.getElementById('threshold-out');\n  var testedCountEl = document.getElementById('tested-count');\n  var stoppedEl = document.getElementById('stopped');\n  var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n  var hypotheses = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('.hypothesis'));\n\n  function reset() {\n    hypotheses.forEach(function (h) {\n      h.classList.remove('tested', 'stopped-here', 'untested');\n    });\n  }\n\n  function update() {\n    reset();\n    var threshold = +thresholdSlider.value;\n    thresholdOut.textContent = threshold + '%';\n\n    var testedCount = 0;\n    var stoppedAt = null;\n    var stoppedIndex = -1;\n\n    for (var i = 0; i < hypotheses.length; i++) {\n      var prob = +hypotheses[i].getAttribute('data-prob');\n      var label = hypotheses[i].getAttribute('data-label');\n\n      testedCount++;\n      hypotheses[i].classList.add('tested');\n\n      if (prob >= threshold) {\n        hypotheses[i].classList.add('stopped-here');\n        stoppedAt = 'Explanation ' + label + ' (' + prob + '%)';\n        stoppedIndex = i;\n        for (var j = i + 1; j < hypotheses.length; j++) {\n          hypotheses[j].classList.add('untested');\n        }\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n\n    testedCountEl.textContent = testedCount;\n    stoppedEl.textContent = stoppedAt || 'none';\n\n    if (stoppedAt) {\n      var untestedCount = hypotheses.length - stoppedIndex - 1;\n      if (untestedCount === 0) {\n        caption.textContent = 'The most likely explanation crossed the bar immediately. Search stopped there—no alternatives were tested.';\n      } else if (threshold <= 30) {\n        caption.textContent = 'A low bar means the first explanation tested is plausible enough. Search stops. ' + untestedCount + ' rarer explanations remain invisible.';\n      } else if (threshold >= 65) {\n        caption.textContent = 'A high bar forces testing more alternatives before one qualifies as plausible. ' + untestedCount + ' still went untested after the first crossed.';\n      } else {\n        caption.textContent = 'The first explanation that crosses the bar stops the search. ' + untestedCount + ' rarer explanations remain untested because the initial answer was good enough.';\n      }\n    } else {\n      caption.textContent = 'No explanation crossed the bar. All five were tested and rejected—the system exhausted its options without finding a plausible answer.';\n    }\n  }\n\n  thresholdSlider.addEventListener('input', update);\n  update();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
